based upon the first half of the 20th century.

251
0:12:02.16,000 --> 0:12:04,000
So growth can wash away

252
0:12:04.16,000 --> 0:12:07,000
even what appears to be a great depression.

253
0:12:07.16,000 --> 0:12:09,000
Alright. What else?

254
0:12:09.16,000 --> 0:12:12,000
Oil. Oil. This was a big topic.

255
0:12:12.16,000 --> 0:12:19,000
When I was writing up my notes oil was $140 per barrel.

256
0:12:19.16,000 --> 0:12:22,000
So people were asking a question. They were saying,

257
0:12:22.16,000 --> 0:12:26,000
"Is China drinking our milkshake?"

258
0:12:26.16,000 --> 0:12:27,000
(Laughter)

259
0:12:27.16,000 --> 0:12:3,000
And there is some truth to this,

260
0:12:30.16,000 --> 0:12:34,000
in the sense that we have something of a finite resource,

261
0:12:34.16,000 --> 0:12:37,000
and increased growth is going to push up demand for that.

262
0:12:37.16,000 --> 0:12:39,000
But I think I don't have to tell this audience

263
0:12:39.16,000 --> 0:12:44,000
that a higher price of oil is not necessarily a bad thing.

264
0:12:44.16,000 --> 0:12:47,000
Moreover, as everyone knows,

265
0:12:47.16,000 --> 0:12:5,000
look -- it's energy, not oil, which counts.

266
0:12:50.16,000 --> 0:12:52,000
And higher oil prices mean

267
0:12:52.16,000 --> 0:12:55,000
a greater incentive to invest in energy R&D.

268
0:12:55.16,000 --> 0:12:57,000
You can see this in the data.

269
0:12:57.16,000 --> 0:13:,000
As oil prices go up, energy patents go up.

270
0:13:00.16,000 --> 0:13:02,000
The world is much better equipped

271
0:13:02.16,000 --> 0:13:04,000
to overcome an increase in the price of oil

272
0:13:04.16,000 --> 0:13:06,000
today, than ever in the past,

273
0:13:06.16,000 --> 0:13:08,000
because of what I'm talking about.

274
0:13:08.16,000 --> 0:13:12,000
One idea, one world, one market.

275
0:13:12.16,000 --> 0:13:15,000
So I'm optimistic

276
0:13:15.16,000 --> 0:13:17,000
so long as we hew to these two ideas:

277
0:13:17.16,000 --> 0:13:19,000
to keep globalizing world markets,

278
0:13:19.16,000 --> 0:13:23,000
keep extending cooperation across national boundaries,

279
0:13:23.16,000 --> 0:13:26,000
and keep investing in education.

280
0:13:26.16,000 --> 0:13:29,000
Now the United States has a particularly important role

281
0:13:29.16,000 --> 0:13:32,000
to play in this:

282
0:13:32.16,000 --> 0:13:35,000
to keep our education system globalized,

283
0:13:35.16,000 --> 0:13:39,000
to keep our education system open to students from all over the world,

284
0:13:39.16,000 --> 0:13:41,000
because our education system

285
0:13:41.16,000 --> 0:13:43,000
is the candle

286
0:13:43.16,000 --> 0:13:48,000
that other students come to light their own candles.

287
0:13:48.16,000 --> 0:13:51,000
Now remember here what Jefferson said.

288
0:13:51.16,000 --> 0:13:54,000
Jefferson said, "When they come

289
0:13:54.16,000 --> 0:13:57,000
and light their candles at ours,

290
0:13:57.16,000 --> 0:14:02,000
they gain light, and we are not darkened."

291
0:14:02.16,000 --> 0:14:05,000
But Jefferson wasn't quite right, was he?

292
0:14:05.16,000 --> 0:14:08,000
Because the truth is,

293
0:14:08.16,000 --> 0:14:12,000
when they light their candles at ours,

294
0:14:12.16,000 --> 0:14:16,000
there is twice as much light available for everyone.

295
0:14:16.16,000 --> 0:14:2,000
So my view is: Be optimistic.

296
0:14:20.16,000 --> 0:14:23,000
Spread the ideas. Spread the light.

297
0:14:23.16,000 --> 0:14:25,000
Thank you.

298
0:14:25.16,000 --> 0:14:28,000
(Applause)

